   stable structures are stabilized subsets of these streams.

3. Collapse Inevitability:
   Any recursive pattern has a probability of collapsing, governed by internal factors such as clarity (Ïƒ_ğ“¢), entropy (ğ“¢), and phase 
   topologyâ€”not by external observation.

4. Qualia Gravity:  
   Gravity is an emergent effect caused by gradients in the qualia substrate. The gravitational field is Ä(x, t) = â€“âˆ‡ğ“º_str(x, t). Forces are a 
   qualia phenomenon.

